 \Big( 1 + \frac{1-r}{n} \Big)^n \to \e^{1-r}. 
 \e^{1-r} - \e^{-r} = (\e-1) \cdot \e^{-r}, 
 \sum_{r \geqslant 1} \e^{1-r} = \frac{1}{1 - \frac{1}{\e}} = \frac{\e}{\e - 1}. 
